@startuml seq-tree
'' ============================================================================
'' vinary-viewer — Sequence: file-tree delivery + client-side filtering.
''
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because: this flow has two distinct triggers (initial
'' open vs. filter keystroke) that share a downstream render, and the filter path
'' never touches main — it is a pure app-db update that force-expands matching
'' folders. PlantUML `== phase ==` dividers separate the two triggers while
'' keeping one `file-tree` lifeline; Mermaid would need two disconnected diagrams.
'' The delivery phase also branches (git root vs. synthetic directory root), which
'' PlantUML expresses as a native `alt` on the same lifelines.
'' ============================================================================
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title File-tree — delivery (`vv:tree`) + filter (`:tree/filter`)

autonumber "0:"

actor User #white
participant "main.service" as Svc MAIN_TINT
participant "git CLI" as Git FS_TINT
participant "main.dir-walk\n(fs)" as Walk FS_TINT
participant "preload `window.vv`" as Vv IPC_TINT
participant "re-frame\nevents/subs" as RF REFRAME_TINT
participant "app.db\n(:ui :projects /\n :ui :tree-filter)" as Db APPDB_TINT
participant "ui.tree\nfile-tree" as Tree RENDERER_TINT

== delivery (on open) ==
Svc -> Git : `rev-parse --show-toplevel`\n(cwd = file's dir)
Git --> Svc : repo root, or nothing

alt the file is inside a git repository
  Svc -> Git : `ls-files --cached --others --exclude-standard`\n(cwd = repo root)
  Git --> Svc : tracked & untracked-not-ignored paths
  Svc -> Svc : {root, files, synthetic?=**false**}
else no repo / git unavailable
  Svc -> Walk : adopt the containing directory\n(a directory is its own root;\na filesystem root is refused)
  Walk -> Walk : breadth-first walk, bounded\n(<latex>D \le 6</latex>, <latex>N \le 5000</latex>);\nskip dotted + heavy dirs;\nresolve symlinks, never descend them
  Walk --> Svc : {root=**realpath**'d, files,\nsynthetic?=**true**}
end

Svc -> Vv : `webContents.send`\n**vv:tree** {root, files, synthetic?}
Vv -> RF : `onTree` → dispatch `[:tree/received]`
RF -> Db : `projects/merge-project`\n(upsert by root; a covered synthetic\nroot MERGES into its coverer)
Db -> Tree : `:ui/projects` sub fires
Tree -> Tree : per project: `build-tree`\n(flat paths → nested map)\n→ collapsible `<details>` hiccup
Tree --> User : sidebar shows one tree per project

== filter (per keystroke) ==
User -> Tree : type in "Filter files…"
Tree -> RF : dispatch `[:tree/filter q]`
RF -> Db : `assoc-in [:ui :tree-filter] q`
Db -> Tree : `:ui/tree-filter` sub fires
Tree -> Tree : across ALL projects, keep files whose\npath `includes?` (lower-case q);\nmatching folders `:open true`
Tree --> User : narrowed, force-expanded tree

note over Svc, Walk
  Every local open sends a tree — a git root when there is one,
  else the containing directory as a **synthetic** root. Archive
  (`vv-archive://`) and remote (`ssh://`) URIs are excluded before
  `send-tree!` is reached, so they synthesize nothing.
end note

note over RF, Db
  A git root is a **fact**; a synthetic root is an **inference**.
  Containment therefore only ever removes synthetic roots: a repo
  nested inside a browsed directory stays its own project.
  A synthetic root covered by another does not duplicate it — its
  walked subtree is re-based and merged in, so the file you just
  opened is always in the tree (the `--others` invariant).
  Removal is manual — project header ⟶ *Remove from Files*.
end note

legend right
  |= Colour |= Concept |
  |<#3A5BA0>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| MAIN (service) |
  |<#9F8766>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| git CLI / fs walk |
  |<#B1951D>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| IPC seam |
  |<#4F97D7>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| re-frame |
  |<#7590DB>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| app-db (projects + filter) |
  |<#2D9574>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| Renderer / UI |
endlegend
@enduml
